Yes, sure it's a bug!

PlainXref.lex has a number of patterns that start with {FNameChar}+. The generated parser will read the entire line before it sees that it cannot match the rest of the pattern. It then ends up matching it with the . rule, which consumes one character. Then it continues on the second character on the line, again reads the entire line, gives up, and finds a match with the . rule. And so on, and so on...
Adding a rule {FNameChar}+ that just copies the matched region to the output file makes the parsing go much faster because it avoids much of the needless backtracking. (This won't interfere with the rules whose patterns begin with {FNameChar}+, since JFlex will always pick the longest match.)
Fixed in changeset 923:57d2aa303158.
